<Desc><entry>A partnership between Sheffield City Council, Sheffield Hallam University and University of Sheffield which manages Kelham Island Museum (see separate entry), Abbeydale Industrial Hamlet and the Shepherds Wheel.  Organises an events programme each year, the main event being The Victorian Market in December.  During school holidays, on Tuesdays and Wednesdays, there are children's activities at Kelham Island Museum.  In the summer there are 4 themed Living History Sundays at Abbeydale Industrial Hamlet.  Please contact for further information about school education programmes.</entry>
